About Us
 
Associated Products Company, Inc., was founded in 1962 by Chris Sarvis and John Ruth. Throughout the years the firm has grown and been joined by Thomas Sarvis and Dan Sarvis bringing additional sales and customer support.
 
Associated Products today is a manufacturers representative and specialty contractor, providing a complete vertical market approach by assisting Architects, Engineers, and Interior Designers as to product application, complete bidding and installation of the specialty products.
With Akron serving as World Headquarters, a Cleveland Office has been maintained for 25 years. The market served is Northeastern Ohio with seven employees plus an installation group.

Involvement in the business community is centered around memberships in the Builders Exchange of Akron and Cleveland, Construction Specifications Institute (CSI), the American Subcontractors Association (ASA), as well as participation in the AIA and SARA activities. 



 











 






